Planet Waves Portmaster Release (https://github.com/christianhaitian/PortMaster) 
=========================

Original version by:
	https://github.com/Escada-Games/planet-waves

Portmaster Version: 	

- tekkenfede (https://github.com/Tekkenfede/planet-waves-handhelds)
	
Special thanks to: Portmaster Team For helping me testing the cursor system and the game.
To compile:
===========

wget https://downloads.tuxfamily.org/godotengine/3.5.2/godot-3.5.2-stable.tar.xz
tar xf godot-3.5.2-stable.tar.xz
cd godot-3.5.2-stable/platform
git clone https://github.com/Cebion/frt.git
cd ../
scons platform=frt tools=no target=release use_llvm=yes module_webm_enabled=no -j12
strip bin/godot.frt.opt.llvm

Instructions:
=============

To run the game start waves.sh from your ports folder.


Controls:
=============

back = Pause
a = Move planet right 
b = mouse_right/cancel
x = mouse_left/confirm
y = move planet left
l1 = 5 (building n.5)
r1 = mouse_slow
up = 1 (building n.1)
down = 2 (building n.2)
left = 3 (building n.3)
right = 4 (building n.4)
left_analog_up = mouse_movement_up
left_analog_down = mouse_movement_down
left_analog_left = mouse_movement_left
left_analog_right = mouse_movement_right
right_analog_up = mouse_left/confirm
right_analog_down = mouse_right/cancel
right_analog_left = move planet left
right_analog_right = move planet right
for the buildings you can click or use the buttons as shorcut
